    {
      "id": "RQ-0047",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Propagate repo context through task-level webhook notifications",
      "description": "Principles violated: H (operational hygiene), J (consistency/integrity), G (least astonishment). Task-level webhook helpers still build `WebhookContext::default()` even when call sites already know the repo root and task execution context, and failure persistence falls back to the current working directory when `repo_root` is absent. Why it matters: failed-delivery diagnostics and replay can be attributed to the wrong repo in multi-repo or moved-repo workflows, and task-level failure records lose branch/commit context that loop-level events already preserve. Minimal fix: route task start/complete/reject notifications through the context-carrying variants and make repo-root persistence explicit instead of relying on cwd fallback. Acceptance criteria: task-level webhook payloads include repo_root at a minimum, failure-store persistence no longer depends on cwd for normal task events, and focused webhook payload/diagnostics tests pass.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "maintenance",
        "webhook",
        "diagnostics"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/webhook/notifications.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/context.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/cli/task/status.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/webhook/diagnostics/failure_store.rs"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: crates/ralph/src/webhook/notifications.rs:29-49 :: send_webhook constructs payloads with WebhookContext::default() for task-level helpers",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/commands/run/context.rs:56-74 :: mark_task_doing uses notify_task_started without propagating resolved repo context",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/cli/task/status.rs:107-150 :: handle_done and handle_reject emit task webhooks without repo context even though resolved data is available",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/webhook/diagnostics/failure_store.rs:216-229 :: resolve_repo_root_from_runtime falls back to current_dir whenever payload.context.repo_root is absent"
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Introduce or reuse task-level webhook helpers that accept explicit WebhookContext and thread resolved repo_root, branch, and other cheap context through existing call sites.",
        "Reduce failure-store reliance on cwd fallback for normal task events so diagnostics stay attached to the emitting repo.",
        "Add focused webhook payload and diagnostics tests that assert task-level events persist repo_root and resolve failure-store paths from payload context.",
        "Verify by running the relevant webhook payload and diagnostics tests and confirming task-level failure records no longer depend on cwd fallback."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "scan: parallel run bookkeeping, worker workspace sync, git push/rebase races, and webhook delivery retries/redaction",
