    {
      "id": "RQ-0048",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Skip parallel webhook dispatcher startup when webhooks are disabled or unconfigured",
      "description": "Principles violated: A (KISS), B (YAGNI), H (operational hygiene). Parallel preflight unconditionally starts the webhook runtime, and dispatcher construction does not check whether webhooks are enabled or even have a URL before spawning worker and scheduler threads. Why it matters: every parallel run pays thread and global-runtime overhead even in repos that do not use webhooks, and startup noise or failures can surface for a feature that is effectively off. Minimal fix: gate `init_worker_for_parallel` and dispatcher creation on resolved webhook enablement plus URL presence, and keep diagnostics capacity zero when no runtime is needed. Acceptance criteria: disabled/unconfigured webhook configs do not spawn dispatcher threads during parallel preflight, enabled configs still initialize correctly, and the focused runtime tests cover both gated and active cases.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "maintenance",
        "webhook",
        "parallel"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/orchestration/preflight.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/webhook/worker/runtime/state.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/webhook/worker/runtime/tests.rs"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/orchestration/preflight.rs:135-149 :: parallel preflight always calls init_worker_for_parallel before any webhook event is emitted",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/webhook/worker/runtime/state.rs:78-115 :: dispatcher_for_config_with_factory builds a dispatcher from settings without checking enabled/url first",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/webhook/worker/runtime/tests.rs:120-127 :: thread_spawn_failure_is_recoverable_on_later_attempt uses WebhookConfig::default() and still expects 5 spawned threads on recovery",
        "workflow: cargo test -p ralph-agent-loop webhook::worker::runtime::tests::thread_spawn_failure_is_recoverable_on_later_attempt -- --exact :: current passing test proves default webhook config still drives dispatcher startup"
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Add an explicit resolved-config gate so disabled or URL-less webhook configs do not start the dispatcher in parallel preflight or runtime lookup paths.",
        "Keep dispatcher rebuild behavior unchanged for enabled configs while ensuring diagnostics capacity and counters stay idle when no runtime is active.",
        "Extend runtime tests to cover both gated-off and enabled startup behavior.",
        "Verify by running the focused runtime tests and confirming default webhook config no longer spawns dispatcher threads."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "scan: parallel run bookkeeping, worker workspace sync, git push/rebase races, and webhook delivery retries/redaction",
